# Documentation Standards

- Every doc starts with YAML frontmatter (`---` delimiters)
- Use ATX headings (`#`, `##`, `###`)
- Cross-reference with relative links
- Plans go in `docs/plans/` named `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md`
- Generated docs (`icon-inventory.md`, `components.md`) via `cd ui && npm run docs`
- Update AGENTS.md or cursor rules when adding a new standard doc
- Never include real credentials in examples
- Run `./scripts/doc-fleet.sh` before large doc changes (CI `docs` job uses the same bundle). `human-skills/*.md` index files require line-1 `---` like `docs/`.
